  "notes": [
    "The UC Davis Bachelor of Science in Business offers a core foundation anchored in math, statistics and economics while building competencies in fundamental areas of business. Business majors choose to specialize in one or two of the following areas: Accounting Finance Marketing & Business Analytics Management & Strategy The major is a first-of-its-kind campus partnership between the Graduate School of Management, College of Letters & Science, and College of Agricultural & Environmental Sciences. The Graduate School of Management awards the Bachelor of Science in Business.",
    "Important note: Transfer admission to the Business major will begin fall, 2027. This is a competitive major and is subject to the Selective Major Review process. Transfer students are encouraged to complete as many major preparation courses as possible prior to transfer. Please note the courses that are required for admissions in the below agreement. Please review the Selective Major webpages for additional information on changes to future admissions requirements. Please refer to the Transfer Admissions Requirements for additional information on admissions to this major.",
    "The Business major is closed to TAG . All students interested in applying to the Business major may still submit the transfer UC application in November.",
    "Transfer students are strongly encouraged to work closely with the California Community College counselors for transfer preparation to UC Davis. Transfer students may also contact a UC Davis transfer advisor for assistance. The below agreements should be utilized in conjunction with professional advising.",
    "Please note that the Department Agreements as published on ASSIST are also important documents and should be referenced in conjunction with the major agreements as needed."
  ]
